--- !u!114 &7032605575716292962
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 2302597246166865755}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: c9505e6d3ede8f54d95327965c7035e0, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  HintTexts:
  - If you hold RMB you can charge your attack
  - Hold shift to sprint
  - You can break an enemy's shield using the heavy attack (RMB)
  - Some enemies require a heavy attack to break their defence
  - Hold a heavy attack to deal more damage to enemies within a larger range
  - Bonus damage will be dealt after breaking a shield when holding down the heavy
    attack
  - A heavy attack can effectively take out grouped enemies
  - Heavy attacks are more effective but will slow you down
  - You are unable to use abilities while they are on cooldown
  - 'A shield will prevent all damage from any source '
  - Your shield is invulnerable, but will not last forever
  - Use your heavy attack whilst shielded for extra effect
  - Press Ctrl + Alt + Del for a hidden jumpscare
  - Green spectral walls will require all enemies to be defeated before vanishing
  - The green bar is your stamina, you will struggle to sprint when it is emptied
  - The red bar is your health, it is unadvised to let it drop to zero
  - Avoid breaking the game, it will make some developers cry
  - Look for a green plus on the map when at low HP, it may save you
  - Some enemies may drop healthpacks when defeated, tougher enemies are more likely
    to hold them
  - Your health will only regen when using a healthpack
  - Healthpacks float, spin and glow, is this the work of a ghost?
  - There are health kits scattered around the mall
  - Look for markings across surfaces, they may help you find your way
  - Some ghosts will possess appliances, they are not friendly
  - Avoid people looking at your pin at an ATM, also avoid ATMs which look at you
  - Possessed vending machines do not serve beverages, they serve bullets
  - Keep your eye on certain glowing machines, they may also have an eye on them
  - Some turrets may actively look for a target before shooting
  - Do not get in a staring contest with a turret, you will not win
  - Your tools are too weak to damage possessed machines
  - Contrary to common belief, ghosts can be smacked to deal damage
  - Some ghosts are cowards and may run when confronted
  - Lazers will change colour, while orange lazers will not damage you, red lazers
    will
  - Nuns can be quite dangerous in battle
  - Blue projectiles will hurt you, so will green, just avoid projectiles
  - Shielded enemies hit hard but are vulnerable without their shield
  - 'You can attack and move at the same time, your enemies cannot '
  - Dirty footsteps will reveal the source of your enemies
  - A certain individual is not pleased by your arrival
  - Obstacles will not break when hit, otherwise the mall staff would not be pleased
  - This text is not temporary as otherwise it would not be here
  - You are currently pausing the game, hello
  - We are not all made strong
  - All trees look the same, they are not real
  - You cannot enter tree planters, otherwise the floor would get dirty
  - Not all hints are useful
  - Life is full of open doors, do not try the closed ones, they will not open for
    you
  - Their exists no spelling mistakes, only grammar
  - Less reading, more playing
  - You are not being paid by the hour, get a move on
  - Escalators are elevators with extra steps
  - Do not attempt to converse with your enemies
  - Despite the title, none of the ghosts have experience in retail
  - You are unable to use the arcade machines as you are already playing a game
  - This game is a Hack and Slash. Wraiths do their best now and are preparing
  - If you can't keep moving, start fighting
  - Avoid falling down pits, your legs are not strong
  - Avoid getting hit, your healthbar will thank you!
  - Use the environment to your advantage
  - Do not be still in combat, otherwise your enemies will gladly keep you in that
    state
  - Avoid getting cornered, it may not end well
  - The minimap may reveal entrances not visible
  - The minimap will only show the layout of visited areas
  - 'The minimap will show more than you can see normally '
  - Follow the marker on your map whilst outside of combat to find your goal
  - Listen out for spectral walls disapearing
  - Blue spectral walls require tougher enemies to be slain
  - Red spectral walls are beyond your control
  - Waves of enemies will know your exact position, your only option is to fight
  - Each enemy type is unique on the minimap
  - If the radar is flashing red, an enemy is close by
  - If the radar is flashing green, a healthpack is near
  - A disc icon will appear when you activate a checkpoint
  HintText: {fileID: 7802934577894052326}
